  <p>All About Pets Veterinary Hospital offers laser therapy as a non-invasive, drug-free treatment option for managing pain, reducing inflammation, and promoting healing in pets.</p>

  <h2>How Pet Laser Therapy Works</h2>
  <p>Laser therapy uses focused light energy to stimulate cell regeneration and increase blood circulation. This helps reduce pain and inflammation while speeding up the body's natural healing process. The treatment is painless, and most pets find it relaxing.</p>

  <h3>Conditions Treated with Laser Therapy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Arthritis and joint pain</li>
    <li>Post-surgical healing</li>
    <li>Soft tissue injuries (sprains, strains)</li>
    <li>Skin wounds and infections</li>
    <li>Ear infections</li>
    <li>Chronic pain conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Benefits of Pet Laser Therapy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Non-invasive and painless</li>
    <li>No sedation required</li>
    <li>Can reduce the need for medications</li>
    <li>Fast treatment sessions</li>
    <li>No known side effects</li>
  </ul>

  <p>If your pet is dealing with chronic pain or recovering from surgery, laser therapy may be a good option. Contact us to learn more.</p>
